  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2021-05-25",
    "date": "2021-07-23T17:53:14Z",
    "text": "Recognizing Military Service in PSLF Act\n\nThis bill requires the Department of Education to count each month for which a borrower's federal student loan payment was in deferment or forbearance during a period of active duty, including certain National Guard duty, as a qualifying payment for the purpose of the Public Service Loan Forgiveness (PSLF) program.\n\nUnder current law, a borrower who is a service member is eligible to receive student loan forgiveness under the PSLF program; however, if the borrower places their loan into deferment or forbearance while they are on active duty, that period of time does not count as a qualifying payment for the PSLF program."
  },
